.TH PAI-MODELS 1 "April 2026" "PAI" "PAI User Commands"
.SH NAME
pai-models \- interactive Ollama model picker
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pai-models
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pai-models
is the interactive model browser for PAI. It reports currently
installed Ollama models, recommends a best-fit model for the
machine's RAM, and offers to pull it.
.PP
For the first-boot GUI equivalent, see
.BR pai-model-picker .
For the underlying sizing logic, see
.BR pai-recommend-model .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/pai-models
The executable.
.TP
.I ~/.config/pai/default-model
The currently-selected default Ollama model, written by the picker.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pai-recommend-model (1),
.BR pai-status (1),
.BR ollama (1)
.SH AUTHOR
The PAI project \[em] https://pai.direct
